right-click res/values/ and select New â†’ Values resource file
Enter strings for the File name. Leave the Source set option set to main. Make sure Directory name is set to values.
Select Locale in the Available qualifiers list and click the >> button to move Locale to the Chosen qualifiers section.
Select language in the Language list.

The language configuration qualifiers are taken from ISO 639-1 codes, and each consists of two characters.

directory will be like

res/values-hi/ for hindi


TRANSLATIONS EDITOR

right-click on one of the strings.xml files in the project tool window and select Open Translations Editor

TARGETING A REGION

language-plus-region qualifier
e.g.
    -es-rES -   the qualifier for Spanish spoken in Spain
